-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate returns to one approved return per item (earliest return_date)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    return_id,
    item_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- models/intermediate/int_items_with_category.sql
```sql
-- Join order_items with products and categories to get category_name
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
        ON p.product_id = oi.product_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    order_id,
    product_id,
    quantity,
    category_name
FROM source
```

-- models/fact/fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        i.category_name,
        SUM(i.quantity) AS total_items_sold,
        SUM(COALESCE(r.quantity, 0)) AS total_items_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_category') }} i
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
        ON oi.item_id = i.item_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = i.item_id
    GROUP BY i.category_name
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    total_items_sold,
    total_items_returned,
    CASE
        WHEN total_items_sold = 0 THEN 0
        ELSE total_items_returned::DECIMAL / total_items_sold
    END AS return_rate
FROM source
ORDER BY return_rate DESC
